For {= provider =}+ merchant-capable professional poster-printing providers or print-on-demand platforms, report {= poster_product =}+ materially distinct paper poster product families, catalog items, or SKU families per provider. For each provider/product pairing, supply a public source for each of the {= capability_facet =} capability facets below ({= url =}+ URL under each facet).

The goal is a public evidence atlas of poster-printing capability, not a ranked shortlist, buying recommendation, or implementation guide. Use official provider, platform, catalog, help, file-prep, pricing, turnaround, developer, integration, fulfillment, white-label, or drop-ship pages. Each entry must state the concrete source-backed finding and any visible limit, missing, or conflict state carried by that page.

Capability facets:
{=% for facet, description in capability_facet_descriptions.items() =%}
- `{= facet =}`: {= description =}
{=% endfor =%}

`poster_product` ought to be a paper poster, large-format poster, art print, photo poster, wall print, or comparable paper print product. Canvas, apparel, stickers, framed-only decor, yard signs, banners, foam boards, rigid signage, and purely digital design templates do not count unless the page also exposes a standalone paper-poster or paper-print option.

Treat each `poster_product` as a product-family/SKU-family claim, not as a label scraped from a size selector, consumer category, or navigation flow. Size-only labels (`24 x 36 poster`), orientation-only labels (`horizontal poster`), stock/finish-only labels (`80 lb gloss poster`), upload/design route labels (`upload your own poster`), and generic flow labels (`posters from HOME`, `SHOP posters`) do not count as separate products unless the provider's catalog exposes them as separate product families, catalog items, SKU prefixes, merchant catalog records, product codes, or template groups. If a single product page merely lists size, paper, or orientation options, those options are variants of one submitted poster product.

Requirements:
- The provider must be a professional, POD, print-marketplace, large-format, trade/bulk, API/integration, white-label/drop-ship, or comparable merchant-capable print service with public poster or large-format paper print-order evidence. A consumer-only photo-gift storefront, design tool, or local shop page does not qualify merely because it sells one-off poster prints.
- The page must clearly tie the named provider to the named poster product, product family, catalog item, SKU family, or a poster/print-product route visibly applicable to that product at product-family specificity. Do not stretch a generic poster/category page to support multiple size, paper, orientation, or flow variants as separate products.
- The page must fit the declared capability facet on an official or provider/platform-controlled public source.
- `product_catalog` should be an official product, catalog, SKU, marketplace catalog, API/developer catalog, or product-family page showing a concrete discriminator for the submitted paper-poster family: for example a product code, SKU prefix/family, catalog table row, merchant catalog/product ID, exact provider catalog handle, template group, or comparable source-visible product-family identity. A broad consumer page that only says "posters", "photo prints", paper choices, sizes, prices, or an upload button is not enough.
- `artwork_file` should be product-specific file-prep or template evidence: a template page/download, product-spec table, accepted-format/DPI/bleed/trim guidance, design-file caveat, or help/developer page that visibly applies to the named poster product or its product family. A normal product page with only "upload", "start designing", or a size picker is not enough.
- `commercial_fulfillment` should be product-linked merchant/POD operational evidence beyond ordinary consumer add-to-cart availability or delivery copy: production time or turnaround/SLA, fulfillment region or lab routing, shipping/pickup boundary with a product constraint, minimum order, bulk/trade terms, API/integration ordering, white-label packaging, drop-ship support, quote-only limitations, regional/provider availability, or comparable product-specific operational limits. A page that only shows a price, cart button, "fast shipping", generic shipping FAQ, generic delivery estimate, or generic business/API marketing does not satisfy this facet unless it also ties such operational evidence to the poster product, product family, catalog, or public print-order route.
- A single URL may support more than one facet only when the page has clearly separate product-specific catalog, artwork/template/spec, or operational fulfillment content. One generic poster/category/order page cannot satisfy every product and every facet for a provider merely because it lists poster options, an upload/design button, price, and checkout, shipping, or delivery text.
